cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use geist in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "geist: a dependency-free CPU inference engine and on-device agent for small LLMs"
abstract: >-
  geist is a high-performance, dependency-free inference engine and on-device
  tool-use agent that runs small LLMs (Gemma 4, ternary BitNet b1.58) on the CPU
  as a single static binary — no BLAS, Python, or CUDA — tuned for edge hardware
  such as the Raspberry Pi 5.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Schlegel
    given-names: Germar
    affiliation: "geisten Holding UG (haftungsbeschränkt)"
repository-code: "https://github.com/geisten/geistlib"
url: "https://github.com/geisten/geistlib"
version: "0.3.0"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - llm
  - inference
  - cpu
  - edge
  - quantization
  - bitnet
  - on-device-agent
